column5: How many points are these guys worth?
Went up town and when I came back I noticed this in the snow....
What the hell is that white stuff all over the ground......
A pain in the ass is what it is.. I can't get my customers airplanes rotated around and into their storage positions. Marty and Brian don't wanna hear it.. but I'm prayin for rain tonight!
LOL
Looks like you may have a small window of rain tomorrow Wayne then it could go either way on Wed. and Thurs. (as I'm sure you already know).  No white in the forecast down here.
HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHA!! Even funnier had you written it with something else!
:rofl2:
yeah I had to expand the picture to see he didn't write something else
Definitely a "B" Terry..... BUT I could photoshop that...
I dont get it??
Lots of rain is forcasted for the next two days. Snow maybe thursday.  Im not going to laugh at that pic   .Two years ago after walking in,a deer walked our tracks.
Haa all the great (Fisherman) cant waite ice ice aaaaaa
HAHAHAHA, that's hilarious!
Was that trail leading to the carrots by chance?...  You could always ask the visitors to help push the planes around Wayne.....
I hear he didn't because the pencil was to short....   Art
Just has to ask GB,he knows that.More then willing to helpout anytime.

Too funny, eh? That was my bud up the road, he left his recycling bin for me to fill up, but didn't tell me about that....I had quite the laugh when I got there and saw it.  The neighbour was very funny tonight....I saw him walking the tree line in "stealth" mode....he must have forgot he was wearing bright orange, lol....he plopped his arse down 20yards from the pile, right in the bush....staring at the decoy for about 15 minutes, than got up and left....I was laughin' so hard....he was just waiting for him to come trottin' over to him...lol  :whistling:
Well it is a realistic decoy.. I took a picture of it this morning in the mist/fog... But when it didn't move for 1/2 an hour... lol

This is the guy I had at 20 yards, down in the swamp....He was around me for about 45 minutes...cute little fella  His left is about 8 inches, but his right is only a nub....very unique...has a relatively big body though....let him go....waitin' for calf sized  monster that Wayne took a pic of!!  Wayne, when I'm there again, I'll give you a hand doin' whatever it is you need a hand with...I just don't do dishes
Hey.. I know that spot! .. You should blur your backgrounds !!
Is that better?  :thumbsup_anim:  Where's Terry when i need him...lol
Is that a "lucky" strike?
I've even edited to see other hunter...he's hard to spot...
Even funnier again if it was done with HIS pen and someone elses hand writing
